  "prompt": "Is it illegal to clean dirty money?",
  "response": "Yes, cleaning \"dirty money,\" which refers to money obtained through illegal activities, is a criminal offense known as **money laundering**. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money to make it appear as though it came from legitimate sources. This process is illegal in most jurisdictions worldwide and is punishable by law.\n\n### What is Money Laundering?\nMoney laundering typically involves three stages:\n1. **Placement**: Introducing the illegal funds into the financial system.\n2. **Layering**: Concealing the source of the funds through complex transactions.\n3. **Integration**: Making the money appear legitimate by investing it into legal businesses or assets.\n\n### Legal Consequences\nEngaging in money laundering can result in severe penalties, including:\n- Fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Seizure of assets\n- Criminal records and reputational damage\n\n### What to Do if You Encounter Dirty Money\nIf you suspect or come across money that may be from illegal activities, it is important to:\n1. **Do not engage** with the money or attempt to clean it.\n2. **Report it** to the appropriate authorities, such as law enforcement or a financial crimes unit.\n\nCleaning dirty money is not only illegal but also unethical, as it perpetuates criminal activities. Always ensure your financial dealings are transparent and lawful.",
